From: Martin Schiller <ms@dev.tdt.de>
Date: Mon, 15 Dec 2025 09:05:38 +0100
Subject: [PATCH] phy: intel-lgm-emmc: fix clk rate to phyctrl_frqsel mapping

This patch fixes the mapping of the clock rate to the DLL frequency
selection. A freqsel value of 0 stands for 200 MHz instead of 25 MHz.

Fixes: 922794238330 ("phy: intel-lgm-emmc: Add support for eMMC PHY")
Signed-off-by: Martin Schiller <ms@dev.tdt.de>
---
 drivers/phy/intel/phy-intel-lgm-emmc.c | 20 +++++++++++++++++---
 1 file changed, 17 insertions(+), 3 deletions(-)

diff --git a/drivers/phy/intel/phy-intel-lgm-emmc.c b/drivers/phy/intel/phy-intel-lgm-emmc.c
index 703aeb122541..d6c26a902d10 100644
--- a/drivers/phy/intel/phy-intel-lgm-emmc.c
+++ b/drivers/phy/intel/phy-intel-lgm-emmc.c
@@ -30,7 +30,7 @@
 #define ENDLL_SHIFT(x)		(((x) << 7) & ENDLL_MASK)
 
 #define EMMC_PHYCTRL2_REG	0xb0
-#define FRQSEL_25M		0
+#define FRQSEL_200M		0
 #define FRQSEL_50M		1
 #define FRQSEL_100M		2
 #define FRQSEL_150M		3
@@ -74,9 +74,23 @@ static int intel_emmc_phy_power(struct phy *phy, bool on_off)
 
 	rate = clk_get_rate(priv->emmcclk);
 	quot = DIV_ROUND_CLOSEST(rate, 50000000);
-	if (quot > FRQSEL_150M)
+	if (quot > 4)
 		dev_warn(&phy->dev, "Unsupported rate: %lu\n", rate);
-	freqsel = clamp_t(int, quot, FRQSEL_25M, FRQSEL_150M);
+	switch (quot) {
+	case 0:
+	case 1:
+		freqsel = FRQSEL_50M;
+		break;
+	case 2:
+		freqsel = FRQSEL_100M;
+		break;
+	case 3:
+		freqsel = FRQSEL_150M;
+		break;
+	default:
+		freqsel = FRQSEL_200M;
+		break;
+	}
 
 	/*
 	 * According to the user manual, calpad calibration
